?topicID=681.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: There is more</span><hr size=1> I don't use AIM or ICQ (pesky firewall at work).  I do use IRC from time to time, but not recently.  If you wish to correspond off-board, please feel free (but add your email address to your username, else I've no way to reply to you except for here.)<br>
<br>
The followup has a lot of interesting premises, but to be honest, it's not quite to my taste.  Personal preferences aside, here's what I hope to be an objective c&amp;c on the followup:<br>
<br>
1) whitespace please.  I'm running out of visine. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
2) Sounds like you have a power level difference here, sort of like the Batman / Superman teamups.  What is an annoyance for Kojiiro would kill Cam.  Tex, even if so inclined, would have no way of ruffling Hagane's hair.<br>
<br>
3) While the empire does add another factor here, it may overshadow the whole planetary mob vs. Cam / Tex plot arch.  It's like adding one more airplane to the fleet to take on King Kong - &quot;Crunch all you want - we'll make more.&quot;<br>
<br>
4) The Tar Kin character is still undeveloped and that conflict is unresolved.  I don't see Tar Kin as a separate factor - he's just the Mob's muscle, right?  At worst, the cops will shoot at him as well as Cam &amp; Tex, but if he snarls &quot;I'm working for your boss, you fools!&quot; they'll back off quickly.<br>
<br>
5) There is no mention of Hagane's sword being magical or otherwise being somehow nullfied.  If it's a martial art, then at best you could take away the unique weapon (balance, strength, design) so they can't use it.  (Or just not let them booze up if they're using Drunken Boxing.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )  The arena's negating effects needs to have some justification and ideally, some forewarning.<br>
<br>
I guess the whole thing is a question of scale.  The Cam/Tex portion made it seem very personal, very gritty.  The Kojiiro/Hagane is so much larger than life, it's like putting Casablanca and Superman on the same continuum: &quot;Rick fights the nazis, then retires on a farm where one day...&quot;  It's just jarring.<br>
<br>
By itself, the Kojiiro/Hagane story arc is very well done - it's nice and space / soap-opera-y.  I'm not a fan of external attacks (think Guardian Spirits from the Final Fantasy games) where out of netherspace external monsters / devices / artifacts suddenly appear to decimate the target.  I can accept chi-power, even if it has physical manifestation - hair standing on end, chi-balls, even force-fields.  I would prefer them used sparingly, or not at all.<br>
<br>
I like martial arts films, but not the hokey ones where the combatants scream the name of their super attack before doing it.  (I especially hate the ones where they then have the name in chinese superimposed on the screen, but that's another story...)  <br>
<br>
Superattacks are well, another story.  My version of a superattack would be something so low or so so dishonorable that they're not done.  So you do it, then kill them when they're shocked that you'd knee them in the sack.  No witnesses, no evidence.  But that's me.<br>
<br>
For me, a great example of showing ones martial prowess came at the end of <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Once Upon A Time in China</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, where Jet Li's Wong Fei-Hung kills the villian by flinging a musket ball as you or I would shoot a marble.  It's subdued, and while it's impossible, it shows off the character's abilities rather than the special effects budget.<br>
<br>
One I'm planning to use for one of my stories is an origami master who folds a sheet of paper fine enough and firm enough to cause a paper cut with the fold.  Again, understated, but evidencing impressive ability. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/utaerx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TaerX</A> at: 6/28/02 9:47:21 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/utaerx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TaerX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/28/02 10:44:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=681.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: There is more</span><hr size=1> BTW - going to be gone for the next week.  Hope to see you then.  Good luck on your story and keep working at it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#336699>- </font><a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs>Polykarbon BBS</a><font color=#336699> - </font><a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26>Writer's Forum</a> <font color=#336699> - </font><a href="http://www.polykarbon.com">Polykarbon: Manga & Photoshop</a><font color=#336699> - </font><br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM ARTS AD SCRIPT -->
